--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Language: en_US
insert or replace into EnglishText
    (Tag,                                                             Text)
values
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_IMPERIAL_FREE_CITIES_DESCRIPTION",       "Each city can build one more district than usual (exceeding the normal limit based on [ICON_Citizen] Population). +2 [ICON_Science] Science and +2 [ICON_Culture] Culture for cities that has Specialty Districts."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_HOLY_ROMAN_EMPEROR_DESCRIPTION",               "Additional Military policy slot. Double Influence Points."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_INDONESIA_NUSANTARA_DESCRIPTION",        "Coast and Lake tiles provide a standard adjacency bonus for Holy Site, Campus, Industrial Zone, and Theater Square districts. +1 [ICON_AMENITIES] Amenity from entertainment to each Entertainment Complex adjacent to a Coast or Lake tile."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_GOLDEN_LIBERTY_DESCRIPTION",             "Culture Bomb adjacent tiles when completing an Encampment or Fort inside friendly territory. All Military policy slots in the current government is converted to Wildcard slots. Tiles that adjacent to Encampment gets +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production, Tiles that adjacent to the Fort gets +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production. +20% [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production towards Encampment and its buildings. +4 [ICON_Strength] Combat Strength when Poland has any kind of Alliance."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_LITHUANIAN_UNION_DESCRIPTION",                 "Poland's majority religion becomes the dominant religion in cities that loses a tile to a Polish Culture Bomb. Holy Sites gain standard Faith adjacency bonus instead of minor adjacency bonus from other Districts. +2 [ICON_Gold] Gold, +2 [Icon_Culture] Culture , +2 [Icon_Science] Science , +2 [Icon_Faith] Faith to all Trade routes between Poland and its Alls or Suzerain's City States."),
    --("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_GOLDEN_LIBERTY_DESCRIPTION",             "May purchase Military Engineers with [ICON_Faith] Faith. Military Engineers receive +2 charges. Culture Bomb adjacent tiles when completing an Encampment or Fort inside friendly territory. Tiles that adjacent to Encampment gets +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production, Tiles that adjacent to the Fort gets +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production. [NEWLINE]All Military policy slots in the current government is converted to Wildcard slots. [NEWLINE]Cavalry units have 50% less [ICON_Strength] Combat Strength reduction from being injured."),
    --("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_LITHUANIAN_UNION_DESCRIPTION",                 "+20% [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production towards Encampments, Holysites and their buildings. Poland's majority religion becomes the dominant religion in cities that loses a tile to a Polish Culture Bomb. Holy Sites gain standard Faith adjacency bonus instead of minor adjacency bonus from other Districts. [NEWLINE]+1 [ICON_Culture] Culture for every two grass, plains, grass hills or plains hills tiles in your cities with Civil Service Civic."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_ELEANOR_LOYALTY_DESCRIPTION",                  "Great Works in Eleanor’s cities each cause -2 Loyalty per turn in foreign cities within 9 tiles. A city that leaves another civilization due to a loss of Loyalty and is currently receiving the most Loyalty per turn from Eleanor's civilization skips the Free City step to join this civilization. [NEWLINE]May initiate the Circuses and Bread project in any city with a Theater Square district. Artifact Museum and Art Museum get 3 extra slots in cities built by Eleanor. Artifact Museum and Art Museum are automatically themed when they have all their slots filled."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_NKISI_DESCRIPTION",                      "All land units ignore [ICON_MOVEMENT] movement penalty from Forest and Jungle. +2 [ICON_Food] Food, +2 [ICON_Production] Production, +4 [ICON_Gold] Gold and +1 [ICON_FAITH] from each [ICON_GreatWork_Relic] Relic, [ICON_GreatWork_Artifact] Artifact, and Sculpture [ICON_GreatWork_Sculpture] Great Work of Art in addition to the usual [ICON_Culture] Culture. Receive 100% more [ICON_GreatWriter] Great Writer, [ICON_GreatArtist] Great Artist, [ICON_GreatMusician] Great Musician, and [ICON_GreatMerchant] Great Merchant points. Palace has slots for 5 Great Works."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_BABYLON_DESCRIPTION",                    "[ICON_TechBoosted] Eurekas provide 90% of the [ICON_SCIENCE] Science for technologies. -50% [ICON_SCIENCE] Science per turn."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_MAYAB_DESCRIPTION",                      "Settling adjacent to Fresh Water and Coast does not provide extra [ICON_HOUSING] Housing, instead each Farm provides an additional +1 [ICON_HOUSING] Housing, +1 [ICON_Production] Production for every adjacent Observatory, and +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold. +1 [ICON_AMENITIES] Amenity for every Luxury adjacent to the City Center."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_MUTAL_DESCRIPTION",                            "Reveal plots within 6 tiles of the starting plot. Cities within 6 tiles of the [ICON_Capital] Capital gain +10% to all yields, and when founded receive a builder. Non capital cities within 9 tiles and outside 6 tiles of the [ICON_Capital] Capital yields remain usual. Other non capital cities receive -15% to all yields. +5 [ICON_Strength] Combat Strength to units within 6 tiles of the [ICON_Capital] Capital."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_TRAJANS_COLUMN_DESCRIPTION",                   "All cities start with a Monument building. +25% Construction speed towads builings in the City Center."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_MAORI_MANA_DESCRIPTION",                 "Begin the game with the Sailing and Shipbuilding technologies unlocked and with the ability to enter Ocean tiles. Embarked units gain +2 [ICON_Movement] Movement. Unimproved Woods and Rainforest are +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production. Additional +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production from Mercantilism ,+1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production from Civil Service and +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production from Conservation. Fishing Boats provide +1 [ICON_FOOD] Food and a Culture Bomb to adjacent tiles. [ICON_GreatWriter] Great Writers cannot be earned."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_SAHEL_MERCHANTS_DESCRIPTION",                  "All [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes gain +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold for every flat Desert tile in the origin city. Receive +1 [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Capacity every time you enter a Golden Age."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_ITERU_EXPANSION2_DESCRIPTION",           "Major adjacency bonus for Campuses and Theater Squares if next to a river. +15% [ICON_Production] Production towards districts and wonders if placed next to a River. Does not receive damage from Floods. Each time after finishing consturcting a wonder, receive a free Builder unit."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_MEDITERRANEAN_EXPANSION2_DESCRIPTION",         "Your [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes to other civilizations provide +8 [ICON_Gold] Gold for Egypt. Other civilizations' [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes to Egypt provide +4 [ICON_Food] Food for them and +4 [ICON_Gold] Gold for Egypt. Trading with Allies earns double as many bonus Alliance Points."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_LAST_PROPHET_DESCRIPTION",               "Automatically receive the final [ICON_GreatProphet] Great Prophet when the next-to-last one is claimed (if you have not earned a [ICON_GreatProphet] Great Prophet already). +4 [ICON_Science] Science for each foreign city following Arabia's Religion."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_MENELIK_DESCRIPTION",                          "Receive [ICON_SCIENCE] Science and [ICON_CULTURE] Culture equal to 15% of your [ICON_FAITH] Faith generation in cities founded on Hills. Units receive +4 [ICON_STRENGTH] Combat Strength on Hills."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_VIETNAM_DESCRIPTION",                    "All districts (except city centers) do not remove Forest, Rainforest and Marsh. Receive the following yields for every building and Districts itself on these features: +2 [ICON_Production] Production in Forest, +2 [ICON_Food] Food in Rainforest and +2 [ICON_Science]  in Marsh. Woods can be planted with the Medieval Faires civic."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_GAUL_DESCRIPTION",                       "Mines provide a minor adjacency bonus for all districts, a Culture Bomb of unowned territory, and receive +1 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture. Specialty districts do not receive a minor adjacency for being adjacent to another district."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_MEDITERRANEAN_COLONIES_DESCRIPTION",     "Begin the game with the Writing technology [ICON_TechBoosted] Eureka and Foreign Trade [ICON_CivicBoosted] Boost. Coastal cities founded by Phoenicia and located on the same continent as the Phoenician [ICON_Capital] Capital are 100% Loyal. Settlers gain +2 [ICON_Movement] Movement and +2 sight range while embarked. Settlers ignore additional [ICON_Movement] Movement costs from embarking and disembarking."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_DYNASTIC_CYCLE_EXPANSION2_DESCRIPTION",  "[ICON_TechBoosted] Eurekas and [ICON_CivicBoosted] Inspirations provide 45% of civics and technologies instead of 35%. When completing a wonder receive a random [ICON_TechBoosted] Eureka and [ICON_CivicBoosted] Inspiration from the era of the wonder, if available."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_RAVEN_KING_DESCRIPTION",                       "Levied units gain an ability giving them +2 [ICON_Movement] Movement and +5 [ICON_Strength] Combat Strength. It costs 50% less [ICON_GOLD] Gold and resources to upgrade Levied units. If you Levy troops from a City-State receive 2 [ICON_ENVOY] Envoys with that City-State. Gain the Black Army unique unit when the Castles technology is researched."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_SATRAPIES_DESCRIPTION",                  "+1 [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Route capacity with Political Philosophy civic, gain 1 [ICON_Governor] Governor promotion. Receive +2 [ICON_Gold] Gold and +2 [ICON_Culture] Culture for routes between your own cities. Roads built in your territory are one level more advanced than usual."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_FALL_BABYLON_EXPANSION2_DESCRIPTION",          "+2 [ICON_Movement] Movement for the first 10 turns after declaring a Surprise War on a major civilization. +5 Loyalty per turn in cities with a garrisoned unit. Declaring a Surprise War only counts as a Formal War for the purposes of [ICON_STAT_GRIEVANCE] Grievances and warmongering."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_SCOTTISH_ENLIGHTENMENT_DESCRIPTION",     "Happy cities receive an additional +10%  [ICON_SCIENCE] Science and +10%  [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production. Happy cities generate +2  [ICON_GreatScientist] Great Scientist point per Campus and +2 [ICON_GreatEngineer] Great Engineer point per Industrial Zone. Ecstatic cities double all these amounts."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_RELIGION_CITY_STATES_DESCRIPTION",             "+100% [ICON_FAITH] Faith for 10 turns after declaring a Protectorate War. Each [ICON_ENVOY] Envoy you send to a city-state of your majority Religion counts as two [ICON_ENVOY] Envoys. (Must have a majority Religion)."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_GREAT_MOUNTAINS_DESCRIPTION",            "Citizens may work Mountain tiles. Mountain tiles provide +3 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and. +1 [ICON_FOOD] Food to Mountain tiles for every adjacent Terrace Farm. +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production after researching Construntion."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_PACHACUTI_QHAPAQ_NAN_DESCRIPTION",             "All land units ignore [ICON_MOVEMENT] movement penalty from Hills. Domestic [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes gain +1 [ICON_Food] Food for every Mountain tile in the origin city. Gain the Qhapaq Ñan improvement when Foreign Trade civic is discovered."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_AMAZON_DESCRIPTION",                     "Rainforest tiles provide +1 adjacency bonus for Campus, Commercial Hub, Holy Site, and Theater Square districts, and grant +1 Appeal to adjacent tiles, instead of the usual -1. Lumber Mill provides +1 adjacency bonus for Industrial Zone. Rainforest tiles receive +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production if is adjacent to Industrial Zone tiles. +2 [ICON_CULTURE] for all Rainforest Lumber Mill. After researching Flight, Lumer Mill will provide [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism equal to its [ICON_CULTURE] Culture yields. All districts (except city centers) will not remove Rainforest. +1 [Icon_Faith] Faith if city is adjacent to Rainforest tiles."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_MAGNANIMOUS_DESCRIPTION",                      "After recruiting or patronizing a [ICON_GreatPerson] Great Person, 20% of its [ICON_GreatPerson] Great Person point cost is refunded. +1 [Icon_Faith] Faith in all Rainforest Tiles across your country for every two [ICON_GreatPerson] Great Person you have recruited."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_TREASURE_FLEET_EXPANSION2_DESCRIPTION",  "May form Fleets and Armadas with Exploration and Mercantilism, instead of Nationalism and Mobilization. [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes receive +3 [ICON_Gold] Gold, +2 [ICON_Faith] Faith, and +1 [ICON_Production] Production. [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes between multiple continents receive triple these numbers. Cities not on your original Capital’s continent receive +25% [ICON_Production] Production towards districts and a builder when founded."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_TA_SETI_DESCRIPTION",                    "+30% [ICON_Production] Production toward Ranged units. All Ranged units gain +30% combat experience. Mines over strategic resources provide +1 [ICON_Production] Production. Mines over bonus and luxury resources provide +2 [ICON_Gold] Gold, each kind of mines over bonus and luxury resources provide +10% [ICON_Gold] Gold."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_KANDAKE_OF_MEROE_DESCRIPTION",                 "+20% [ICON_Production] Production towards all districts rising to +30% if there is a Nubian Pyramid adjacent to the City Center."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_GIFTS_FOR_TLATOANI_DESCRIPTION",               "Luxury resources in his territory provide an [ICON_Amenities] Amenity to 2 extra cities. Military units receive +1 [ICON_Strength] Combat Strength when attacking for each different Luxury resource improved in Aztec lands. Combat victories provide [ICON_FAITH] Faith equal to 100% of the Combat Strength of the defeated unit (on Standard Speed)."),
    --("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_FLYING_SQUADRON_DESCRIPTION",                  "Has 1 level of [ICON_VisLimited] Diplomatic Visibility greater than normal with every civilization that she's met. Receives a free Spy (and extra spy capacity) with the Castles technology. All cities can provide +1 spy capacity when city has wonder and chateau. All spies start as Agents with a free promotion. ")
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_SATYAGRAHA_DESCRIPTION",                       "ALL cities +15% growth speed, 15% [ICON_Faith] Faith and +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity when you are at peace with all majors. +5 [ICON_Faith] Faith for each civilization (including India) they have met that has founded a Religion and is not currently at war. Opposing civilizations receive double the war weariness for fighting against Gandhi."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_DHARMA_EXPANSION2_DESCRIPTION",          "Receives Follower Belief bonuses in a city from each Religion that has at least 1 Follower. Cities gain an [ICON_Amenities] Amenity for every Religion with at least 1 Follower. Missionaries have +2 spreads. +100% Religious pressure from your [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes. +0.5 [ICON_Food] Food per Population for cities which have stepwell.")
    ;

